Data analysis techniques including aggregation, trend analysis, and KPI tracking

 Dataset Used
Superstore Dataset
Dataset containing Sales & Profits of a Superstore
Dataset Link:
https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/vivek468/superstore-dataset-final

ðŸ§¹ Data Preparation
To ensure accurate analysis, the dataset was cleaned and structured by:
Removing missing or invalid records
Converting date columns to proper format
Creating a Average Order Value(AOV) column (Sales/Quantity)
Standardizing product and category names

ðŸ“Š Analysis Performed
ðŸ”¹ Revenue Trend Analysis
Monthly and yearly revenue patterns
Identification of seasonal sales trends
ðŸ”¹ Product Performance
Top products by revenue
Contribution of high-performing products
ðŸ”¹ Category Analysis
Revenue comparison across product categories
Identification of key business segments
ðŸ”¹ Regional Analysis
Sales distribution by country/region
High-performing vs underperforming markets
ðŸ”¹ Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)
Total Sales
Total Profits
Average Order Value
Total Quantity

ðŸ’¡ Key Insights
A small group of products contributes significantly to overall revenue.
Certain categories consistently drive higher sales, acting as primary revenue drivers.
Sales follow time-based trends, suggesting seasonal demand patterns.
Some regions generate much higher revenue than others, indicating strong market opportunities.

ðŸ“Œ Business Recommendations
Based on the analysis:
Focus inventory and marketing on top-performing products
Prepare promotions before peak sales periods
Invest more in high-performing regions
Reassess strategy for low-performing categories

ðŸš€ Project Outcome
This project demonstrates how raw  superstore retail sales data can be transformed into a decision-making tool using data analytics and visualization. 
It reflects real-world work done by data analysts in retail and superstore hubs and industries collectively.
